{
  "texts": [
    "III-C, we establish two concrete metrics, namely F 1 best and AU P RC.",
    "F 1 best denotes the highest F1 score calculated under reduced-length point-adjustment when iterating over all possible thresholds.",
    "AU P RC calculates the area under the precision-recall curve generated according to reduced-length point-adjustment, which is widely applied in cases where class imbalance is present in the data.",
    "While F 1 best can measure the best detection performance that the model can achieve on the current test set, AU P RC provides a more nuanced evaluation of the model's performance across different levels of recall, which can be important in anomaly detection.",
    "A model with a higher AU P RC tends to be more robust."
  ]
}